The paper discusses physical layer security in wireless networks, which involves the design of secure transmission strategies and secret-key generation protocols. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI), as well as computer security (cs.CR) and multimedia (cs.MM) due to the need for authentication and encryption. Additionally, the paper covers game theory and stochastic geometry, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
